The paper proposes a method to improve the performance of binarized convolutional neural networks (BCNNs) for mobile and AI chips based applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a GAN, which is a popular technique in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions object tracking, which is a task commonly studied in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
